Scenario: Generate a shell

As a machine learning researcher
I want to be able to generate nesting shells
in order to find the range a species dominates.


Given a non-toroidal world of size [10]
When I compute a shell of [5] with radius 2
Then the result contains:
[3]
[7]


Given a non-toroidal world of size [10, 10]
When I compute a shell of [5, 5] with radius 1
Then the result contains:
[4,4]
[4,5]
[4,6]
[5,6]
[6,6]
[6,5]
[6,4]
[5,4]


Given a non-toroidal world of size [10, 10]
When I compute a shell of [4, 6] with radius 1
Then the result contains:
[3,5]
[3,6]
[3,7]
[4,7]
[5,7]
[5,6]
[5,5]
[4,5]


Given a non-toroidal world of size [10, 10]
When I compute a shell of [5, 5] with radius 2
Then the result contains:
[3,3]
[3,4]
[3,5]
[3,6]
[3,7]
[4,7]
[5,7]
[6,7]
[7,7]
[7,6]
[7,5]
[7,4]
[7,3]
[6,3]
[5,3]
[4,3]


Given a non-toroidal world of size [10, 10]
When I compute a shell of [5, 4] with radius 2
Then the result contains:
[3,2]
[3,3]
[3,4]
[3,5]
[3,6]
[4,6]
[5,6]
[6,6]
[7,6]
[7,5]
[7,4]
[7,3]
[7,2]
[6,2]
[5,2]
[4,2]


Given a non-toroidal world of size [10, 10, 10]
When I compute a shell of [5, 5, 5] with radius 1
Then the result contains:
[4,4,4]
[4,4,5]
[4,4,6]
[4,5,4]
[4,5,5]
[4,5,6]
[4,6,4]
[4,6,5]
[4,6,6]
[6,4,4]
[6,4,5]
[6,4,6]
[6,5,4]
[6,5,5]
[6,5,6]
[6,6,4]
[6,6,5]
[6,6,6]
[5,4,4]
[5,4,5]
[5,4,6]
[5,6,4]
[5,6,5]
[5,6,6]
[5,5,4]
[5,5,6]


Given a non-toroidal world of size [10, 10]
When I compute a shell of [1,1] with radius 2
Then the result contains:
[0,3]
[1,3]
[2,3]
[3,3]
[3,2]
[3,1]
[3,0]


Given a toroidal world of size [5,5]
When I compute a shell of [4,4] with radius 2
Then the result contains:
[0,1]
[0,2]
[1,0]
[1,1]
[1,2]
[1,3]
[1,4]
[2,0]
[2,1]
[2,2]
[2,3]
[2,4]
[3,1]
[3,2]
[4,1]
[4,2]

